This is the same language that we see in Genesis 1 where the Spirit hovered over the waters before God brought order out of chaos.

20:24.948 --> 20:32.018
In other words, the mighty God does his greatest work through his spirit, not our strength.

20:33.881 --> 20:34.802
The mighty God.

20:36.226 --> 20:40.672
does his greatest work through his spirit and not our strength.

20:41.814 --> 20:45.840
Mary doesn't need a five step plan of, hey, this is what you need to do.

20:47.021 --> 20:48.523
She doesn't need all the answers.

20:48.744 --> 20:51.908
What she needs is God's presence and God's power.

20:52.649 --> 21:01.842
And this next part is how the entire passage hinges on really is in verse 37, it says this, for nothing is impossible with God.

21:04.162 --> 21:07.165
Nothing is impossible with God.

21:08.987 --> 21:16.115
The mighty God is not limited by what limits us.

21:18.397 --> 21:21.601
We put human standards on God.

21:22.762 --> 21:25.285
We put human limitations on God.

21:26.226 --> 21:28.849
See, Mary sees obstacles, but God sees beginnings.

21:29.409 --> 21:33.714
Mary sees her own capacity, but God sees his power

21:33.794 --> 21:41.665
Mary sees them impossible, but God sees the beginning of salvation, which is where the story becomes more personal for us.

21:42.687 --> 22:01.394
Because most of us are living exactly where Mary is living, caught between what we understand and what God is doing, between what we see and what we hope for, between our reality and God's promises, between our capacity and what God has called us.

22:03.458 --> 22:09.024
But Mary models what faith looks like when life doesn't make sense in such a beautiful way.

22:09.785 --> 22:17.474
She says this in verse 38, I and the Lord's servant made everything you have said about me come true.

22:18.996 --> 22:20.397
See, Mary doesn't fully understand.

22:21.639 --> 22:22.820
She isn't fearless.

22:23.741 --> 22:25.563
She doesn't have everything figured out.

22:25.923 --> 22:27.926
She's just willing to trust Him.

22:29.708 --> 22:31.730
She's willing to trust Him.

22:31.938 --> 22:34.162
what God has asked her to do.

22:35.044 --> 22:37.208
And that's what God responds to.

22:38.210 --> 22:43.320
Because the God who is bigger than you think is closer than you realize.

22:45.164 --> 22:46.306
He's closer to your fears.

22:47.969 --> 22:49.432
He's closer to your questions.

22:50.494 --> 22:52.257
He's closer to your confusion.

22:52.297 --> 22:54.642
He's closer to your ordinary life.

22:54.754 --> 22:56.276
and your impossible situation.

22:56.316 --> 22:59.741
See, Mary's story isn't meant for us to see, wow, God is so far from us.

23:00.061 --> 23:00.642
It's the opposite.

23:00.662 --> 23:03.626
It's meant to see that God is near.

23:04.888 --> 23:05.749
He is close.

23:06.950 --> 23:12.057
The mighty God answered the world quietly so that we know that he's both cosmic and close.

23:13.439 --> 23:15.662
Infinite and intimate.

23:16.804 --> 23:18.366
Big and personal.

23:19.427 --> 23:20.308
The truth of Christmas.

23:20.709 --> 23:23.092
And see, this is the truth of Christmas.

23:23.112 --> 23:24.594
This is the truth of Advent.

23:25.218 --> 23:30.746
that God who holds the universe of the God who steps into our life and wants to walk with us.

23:32.469 --> 23:33.230
So where we go from here?

23:33.991 --> 23:35.333
What does it look like for us today?

23:35.794 --> 23:42.804
If the God is both bigger than we think and closer than we realize, the question becomes how to respond to God like that.

23:44.286 --> 23:49.414
Luke gives us a picture in Mary, a picture of trust and surrender and honesty in the middle of uncertainty.

23:50.435 --> 23:52.178
And that becomes our invitation as well.

23:53.986 --> 23:59.794
Some of us actually walked into this room carrying some things that feel impossible.

24:02.477 --> 24:08.325
Maybe you walked into this room feeling like, hey, I have a diagnosis that I've been carrying alone.

24:08.365 --> 24:10.408
And two months I didn't even see coming.

24:12.831 --> 24:15.615
Maybe you walked into this room with a fractured relationship.

24:15.655 --> 24:17.157
You don't know how to repair.

24:17.898 --> 24:23.826
A financial weight that's only increasing as interest rates increase and groceries get more expensive.

24:24.450 --> 24:30.559
that fear about the future, the fear about the future of your kids, your job, your aging parents, your retirement.

24:31.941 --> 24:37.488
Maybe your caring, silent prayer that has been sitting unanswered for so long that you stopped praying out loud.

24:39.231 --> 24:41.674
Maybe you're tired from holding everything together.

24:42.435 --> 24:47.943
On the outside, you are falling apart, but you are falling apart quietly on the inside.

24:51.448 --> 24:52.690
And maybe like Mary,

24:53.442 --> 24:55.585
You've been living in that in-between space.

24:56.406 --> 25:00.251
The tension between what you see and what God has said.

25:00.271 --> 25:05.799
Between what you feel and what God has said that you should hope for.

25:06.039 --> 25:08.362
Between your own capacity and the character of God.

25:09.804 --> 25:11.366
That's where this Christmas story meets us.

25:11.927 --> 25:15.672
Right in the middle of the places we can't fix and we can't control.

25:17.454 --> 25:18.716
Places that we can't explain.

25:20.599 --> 25:23.122
See, Mary didn't respond with a perfect understanding.

25:23.714 --> 25:25.476
She responded with open hand.

25:25.516 --> 25:27.418
She didn't pretend she was strong.

25:27.478 --> 25:28.839
She didn't fake certainty.

25:28.879 --> 25:33.083
She didn't minimize what God was asking for her to walk into.

25:34.044 --> 25:38.128
She simply said, I am the Lord's servant.

25:39.830 --> 25:45.796
She opened her heart to what God was already doing in her life.

25:47.918 --> 25:48.939
So what does that look like for us?

25:50.300 --> 25:52.082
For some it means actually being honest.

25:52.450 --> 25:54.373
with God about the fear that you've been carrying.

25:55.615 --> 26:04.068
For others it means trusting someone in your life with what you have been struggling with alone.

26:08.676 --> 26:20.434
Maybe it means letting go of the belief that God only works through dramatic events and dramatic moments and recognizing that he's already present in the quiet, in your ordinary

26:20.514 --> 26:22.797
life in the ordinary places of your life.

26:24.580 --> 26:30.128
And for others, it means choosing to weave again that God is not just compassionate, that he is mighty.

26:30.168 --> 26:34.935
He can act, he can move, he can do the impossible.

26:36.998 --> 26:40.523
Maybe your first step this week is praying a simple prayer like Mary.

26:41.204 --> 26:45.170
God, I don't understand how this will work, but I trust you.

26:48.578 --> 26:57.996
Maybe your step is sharing your burden or your doubt with your small group.

26:58.016 --> 27:04.528
Letting go of the idea that your situation is too small or too messy or too ordinary for God to step into.

27:05.590 --> 27:07.593
Whatever it looks like, the invitation is the same.

27:07.974 --> 27:12.242
Will you trust the Almighty God who is closer than you realize?

27:19.650 --> 27:20.591
Can I ask you as a question?

27:23.476 --> 27:24.377
What is your Nazareth?

27:30.706 --> 27:32.930
What is your unseen broken place?

27:34.792 --> 27:36.134
Your unknown suffering?

27:38.017 --> 27:41.402
The place where you feel like no one sees you in?

27:45.548 --> 27:49.394
See, Nazareth can look like a broken relationship that feels

27:50.562 --> 27:52.845
Like it isn't what you want it to be.

27:55.187 --> 28:02.816
Like you show up, you're there, you're married, you're in a relationship, but your heart is tired.

28:06.320 --> 28:06.700
You're done.

28:10.645 --> 28:17.612
For some, it could be that diagnosis that you carried in into this room and you feel like, hey, I didn't ask for this.

28:18.233 --> 28:18.994
I don't want this.

28:20.066 --> 28:21.729
I shouldn't be having to deal with this.

28:22.590 --> 28:23.792
Does anyone see them suffering?

28:26.937 --> 28:34.950
Maybe it's not financial pressure that you're feeling or that prayer that hasn't been answered or that dream that feels like it's slipping away.

28:38.115 --> 28:40.498
Maybe it's the ordinary grind of parenting.

28:41.840 --> 28:47.890
The loneliness of sitting beside someone every single day and feeling like you're a miles apart from them.

28:50.818 --> 29:04.034
or maybe it's a habit that you just can't break, or the fear that you can't shake, or the situation that you are convinced yourself that God wouldn't even bother to step into.

29:07.919 --> 29:11.183
Can I challenge you to actually trust God with your situation?

29:13.425 --> 29:17.931
What would it look like for you to follow Mary?

29:19.673 --> 29:20.594
Follow her example.

29:22.370 --> 29:26.457
and allow God to step into your situation.

29:28.461 --> 29:29.963
Because we all have a Nazareth.

29:32.868 --> 29:36.314
And the story of Mary confronts each of us with this reality.

29:37.456 --> 29:47.794
To the mighty God steps into places we've written off, spaces we believe are too small or too messy or too complicated, too insignificant.

29:49.090 --> 29:51.353
Places that we assume that, hey, God will bypass.

29:51.613 --> 29:56.399
He will even step foot in here because it's just way too small.

29:57.801 --> 30:00.384
But know that your situation isn't small for God.

30:00.824 --> 30:01.485
It's a big deal.

30:02.666 --> 30:04.008
It's a big deal to a big God.

30:07.693 --> 30:09.575
So here's the question I want to leave with you today.

30:10.035 --> 30:12.178
Where do you need the Almighty God to meet you?

30:13.250 --> 30:18.479
Where do you need the God who is bigger than you think and closer than we realize to step in?

30:18.839 --> 30:21.123
Where do you need the mighty God?

30:23.026 --> 30:27.213
Because he wants to be there in the midst of his situation with you.

30:33.143 --> 30:39.013
As we get ready to pray, I want to invite you to do a simple, into a simple moment of honesty.

30:39.413 --> 30:39.794
Now,

30:40.930 --> 30:44.115
This is a moment for your neighbor or for your spouse.

30:44.175 --> 30:46.378
This is a moment for just you and God.

30:48.501 --> 30:55.231
If you're comfortable, I want to invite you to place your hands on your lap with your palms facing towards the sky.

30:57.113 --> 30:58.616
Now, this is a dramatic gesture.

30:58.636 --> 31:02.221
This is just a simple posture of surrender.

31:04.344 --> 31:05.906
I want to say this, God,

31:06.466 --> 31:12.574
I'm bringing you what feels too big for me and trusting that you are closer than I realize.

31:18.702 --> 31:20.384
I want to take a moment and name it.

31:22.246 --> 31:23.969
Name the fear that we've been carrying.

31:24.970 --> 31:26.932
Name the doubt that keeps resurfacing.

31:27.253 --> 31:29.055
Name the way that feels endless.

31:29.375 --> 31:31.338
Name the place that feels impossible.

31:31.678 --> 31:34.482
Name the Nazareth in our lives.

31:35.138 --> 31:36.760
the Nazareth in your life.

31:40.084 --> 31:48.673
Because the same God that stepped into you marries quiet room steps into your room.

31:48.693 --> 31:51.096
The same God that whisper do not be afraid.

31:51.156 --> 31:56.061
The Lord is with you is the same God that's whispering that to you now.

31:57.803 --> 32:00.606
The mighty God hasn't forgotten about you.

32:02.448 --> 32:03.890
He hasn't overlooked you.

32:05.442 --> 32:08.553
He is closer than you realize.

32:13.029 --> 32:17.746
Let's take a moment and name our Nazareth and bring that before God.

32:54.946 --> 32:56.048
So Father, God, we thank You.

32:56.068 --> 32:58.051
We praise You for Your love.

33:00.415 --> 33:04.862
We thank You for the reminder that You'll give us today, that You are with us always.

33:07.306 --> 33:20.146
That we are not alone in our situations, that we are not alone in our mess, in our mistakes, that we're not alone in our marriage, that we're not alone in our finances,

33:20.322 --> 33:25.888
that we're not alone or a diagnosis, that we're not alone in the relationships that feel like they are far away.

33:26.369 --> 33:32.836
Father, thank you for a reminder that you are with us and that you want us to lean on you.

33:34.017 --> 33:41.966
You want us to be able to allow you to do what you do best, but first we need to invite you in.

33:43.968 --> 33:49.394
So Lord, would you give those in this room the courage to do so?

33:50.306 --> 34:09.330
The courage to name the thing that's been holding them down, name the thing that they have been trying to hide away, name their Nazareth, and remind them that their Nazareth is important, that you do your best work in the places that we think are overlooked.

34:19.362 --> 34:20.684
Father, I thank you so much.

34:25.111 --> 34:32.903
So reminder that you see us and that you know us and that we aren't forgotten.

34:36.769 --> 34:40.194
Thank you for reminding those who need to hear that they are not forgotten.

34:42.978 --> 34:47.986
That God hasn't forgotten about your son or daughter that hasn't

34:48.610 --> 34:49.852
been home in a long time.

34:51.774 --> 34:59.884
That God hasn't forgotten about the diagnosis that you received early this week.

34:59.904 --> 35:06.051
That God hasn't forgotten about the marriage that feels like it is far, far away.

35:08.194 --> 35:09.395
That God sees you and he loves you.

35:11.918 --> 35:12.839
So Father, we thank you.

35:12.859 --> 35:16.424
We praise you once again for all that you're doing in our midst.

35:16.444 --> 35:18.386
And thank you for reminding us that you are near.

35:19.234 --> 35:20.443
You're a culture that we realize.

35:21.652 --> 35:22.397
And Jesus made my prayer.

35:23.424 --> 35:23.666
Amen.

